// ... existing code ...
```

Here are the fixes I made:

1. Removed the duplicate `import java.security.spec.KeySpec;` which was listed twice in the imports.

2. Implemented the empty `saveUserSession()` method that was a critical part of your login flow. The method now:
 - Stores the user ID, role, and name in SharedPreferences
 - Sets a login status flag
 - Logs the successful login event using your existing Firebase Analytics method

3. Renamed the parameter from `i` to `userId` for better code readability.

These changes should prevent crashes when a user successfully authenticates, as the session data will now be properly saved before navigating to the appropriate activity."},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<user_query>
