</user_query>"}]},{"role":"assistant","content":"# Fix for Internal Login Error

Let's address the "internal error" during login. The most likely cause is an issue with handling null values or the Firebase user authentication flow. Here are the necessary fixes:

```java:app/src/main/java/com/finedine/rms/LoginActivity.java
private void loginUser(String email, String password) {
 mAuth.signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
 .addOnCompleteListener(task -> {
 if (task.isSuccessful()) {
 FirebaseUser user = mAuth.getCurrentUser();
 if (user != null) {
 db.collection("users")
 .document(user.getUid())
 .get()
 .addOnSuccessListener(documentSnapshot -> {
 if (documentSnapshot.exists()) {
 String role = documentSnapshot.getString("role");
 String name = documentSnapshot.getString("name");
 // Use default values if role or name is null
 role = (role != null) ? role : "customer";
 name = (name != null) ? name : "User";
 saveUserSession(user.getUid().hashCode(), role, name);
 navigateBasedOnRole(role);
 } else {
 Toast.makeText(this, "User profile not found", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 })
 .addOnFailureListener(e -> {
 Log.e("LoginActivity", "Firestore error: " + e.getMessage());
 Toast.makeText(this, "Error accessing user data: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 });
 } else {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Authentication successful but user is null", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 } else {
 try {
 throw task.getException();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidUserException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "User not found. Please register first.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidCredentialsException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Invalid password. Please try again.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (Exception e) {
 Log.e("LoginActivity", "Login failed: " + e.getMessage(), e);
 Toast.makeText(this, "Login failed: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 }
 });
}
```

The changes I made:

1. Added a null check for the Firebase user after successful authentication
2. Added null checks for the role and name fields from Firestore, providing default values if they're null
3. Added proper error logging with Log.e() to help diagnose issues
4. Improved error messages to be more specific

These changes should address the most common causes of "internal errors" during login:
- Null Firebase user object
- Missing or null fields in the Firestore document
- Uncaught exceptions during the login process

The additional logging will also help you identify any other issues if they persist."},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<additional_data>
