Based on the provided code and issue description, I'll fix the login functionality to properly route users to the correct activities based on their roles. The main issues appear to be related to Firebase authentication and navigation.

```java:app/src/main/java/com/finedine/rms/LoginActivity.java
private void loginUser(String email, String password) {
 // Show a loading indicator
 DialogUtils.showProgressDialog(this, "Logging in...");

 mAuth.signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
 .addOnCompleteListener(task -> {
 // Hide loading indicator
 DialogUtils.hideProgressDialog(null);

 if (task.isSuccessful()) {
 FirebaseUser user = mAuth.getCurrentUser();
 if (user != null) {
 Log.d("LoginActivity", "Login successful, fetching user data for: " + user.getUid());

 db.collection("users")
 .document(user.getUid())
 .get()
 .addOnSuccessListener(documentSnapshot -> {
 if (documentSnapshot.exists()) {
 String role = documentSnapshot.getString("role");
 String name = documentSnapshot.getString("name");

 // Use default values if role or name is null
 role = (role != null) ? role : "customer";
 name = (name != null) ? name : "User";

 // Save user session data
 saveUserSession(user.getUid(), role, name);

 // Navigate based on role
 navigateBasedOnRole(role);
 } else {
 Toast.makeText(this, "User profile not found, creating default profile", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 // Create default user profile
 createDefaultUserProfile(user.getUid());
 }
 })
 .addOnFailureListener(e -> {
 Log.e("LoginActivity", "Firestore error: " + e.getMessage());
 Toast.makeText(this, "Error accessing user data: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 });
 } else {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Authentication successful but user is null", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 } else {
 try {
 throw task.getException();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidUserException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "User not found. Please register first.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidCredentialsException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Invalid password. Please try again.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (Exception e) {
 Log.e("LoginActivity", "Login failed: " + e.getMessage(), e);
 Toast.makeText(this, "Login failed: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 }
 });
}

private void saveUserSession(String userId, String role, String name) {
 SharedPreferences sharedPreferences = getSharedPreferences("UserSession", MODE_PRIVATE);
 SharedPreferences.Editor editor = sharedPreferences.edit();
 editor.putString("userId", userId);
 editor.putString("role", role);
 editor.putString("name", name);
 editor.putBoolean("isLoggedIn", true);
 editor.apply();

 // Log successful login
 logLoginEvent("email", true);

 Log.d("LoginActivity", "User session saved. Role: " + role + ", Name: " + name);
}

private void createDefaultUserProfile(String userId) {
 // Create a default profile for the user
 Map<String, Object> userData = new HashMap<>();
 userData.put("role", "customer");
 userData.put("name", "User");
 userData.put("createdAt", new Date());

 db.collection("users")
 .document(userId)
 .set(userData)
 .addOnSuccessListener(aVoid -> {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Default profile created", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 // Save session and navigate
 saveUserSession(userId, "customer", "User");
 navigateBasedOnRole("customer");
 })
 .addOnFailureListener(e -> {
 Log.e("LoginActivity", "Error creating user profile: " + e.getMessage());
 Toast.makeText(this, "Error creating profile: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 });
}

private void navigateBasedOnRole(String role) {
 Intent intent;
 Log.d("LoginActivity", "Navigating based on role: " + role);

 switch (role){
 case "waiter":
 intent = new Intent(this, OrderActivity.class);
 break;
 case "chef":
 intent = new Intent(this, KitchenActivity.class);
 break;
 case "manager":
 intent = new Intent(this, ManagerDashboardActivity.class);
 break;
 default: // customer
 intent = new Intent(this, ReservationActivity.class);
 }

 // Add flags to clear activity stack
 intent.setFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK | Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_CLEAR_TASK);
 startActivity(intent);
 finish();
}
```

These changes fix several critical issues:

1. **Fixed the `saveUserSession` method:**
 - Changed parameter type from `int` to `String` for userId to properly store the Firebase UID
 - Added proper logging to track session saving

2. **Improved error handling:**
 - Added loading indicators using `DialogUtils`
 - Added comprehensive logging to identify issues
 - Improved error messages in Toast notifications

3. **Added fallback for missing user profiles:**
 - Added `createDefaultUserProfile` method to handle cases where authentication succeeds but no user document exists
 - This prevents crashes due to missing user data

4. **Improved navigation:**
 - Added activity flags to prevent navigation issues
 - Added logging to track navigation flow
 - Fixed ReservationActivity navigation for customers (previously was just named "Reservation")

5. **Added null checks:**
 - Properly handled null values from Firestore
 - Provided default values for critical fields

These changes should resolve the internal error during login and ensure proper navigation to the right activity based on user roles."}]}

