</user_query>"}]},{"role":"assistant","content":"Based on your description, it sounds like you're having an issue with the login functionality in your app. The issue is likely related to how the user data is being stored and retrieved. Let me provide a focused fix:

```java:app/src/main/java/com/finedine/rms/LoginActivity.java
// Update your login verification code in LoginActivity:

// In your login button click handler or authentication method
private void loginUser(String email, String password) {
 // Get Firebase Authentication instance
 FirebaseAuth mAuth = FirebaseAuth.getInstance();

 // Show progress dialog
 DialogUtils.showProgressDialog(this, "Logging in...");

 // Authenticate with Firebase
 mAuth.signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
 .addOnCompleteListener(task -> {
 // Hide progress dialog
 // (Make sure you have a reference to your progress dialog)

 if (task.isSuccessful()) {
 // Login successful, get the current user
 FirebaseUser user = mAuth.getCurrentUser();

 // After successful authentication, fetch user data from Firestore
 FirebaseFirestore.getInstance().collection("users")
 .document(user.getUid())
 .get()
 .addOnSuccessListener(documentSnapshot -> {
 if (documentSnapshot.exists()) {
 // Extract user data like role
 String role = documentSnapshot.getString("role");
 String name = documentSnapshot.getString("name");

 // Store in SharedPreferences
 SharedPrefsManager prefsManager = new SharedPrefsManager(this);
 prefsManager.saveUserSession(user.getUid().hashCode(), role, name);

 // Navigate based on role
 navigateBasedOnRole(role);
 } else {
 // User document not found
 Toast.makeText(this, "User profile not found", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 })
 .addOnFailureListener(e -> {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Error: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 });
 } else {
 // Login failed
 try {
 throw task.getException();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidUserException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "User not found. Please register first.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (FirebaseAuthInvalidCredentialsException e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Invalid password. Please try again.", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 } catch (Exception e) {
 Toast.makeText(this, "Login failed: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
 }
 }
 });
}

private void navigateBasedOnRole(String role) {
 Intent intent;
 switch (role) {
 case RoleManager.ROLE_MANAGER:
 intent = new Intent(this, ManagerDashboardActivity.class);
 break;
 case RoleManager.ROLE_CHEF:
 intent = new Intent(this, KitchenActivity.class);
 break;
 case RoleManager.ROLE_WAITER:
 intent = new Intent(this, OrderActivity.class);
 break;
 default:
 intent = new Intent(this, OrderActivity.class);
 break;
 }
 startActivity(intent);
 finish();
}
```

The key issue appears to be that during the registration process, the user is created in Firebase Authentication, but when attempting to log in, there might be a mismatch between the authentication data and how you're retrieving the user information.

Make sure that:

1. Your registration process is correctly saving user details to both Firebase Authentication and Firestore
2. Your login process is properly querying both systems
3. You're using consistent data formats (same email format, same collection names) in both processes

This solution assumes you're using Firebase Authentication and Firestore for user management, which is a common approach given your Firebase dependencies."}]}
